The paper deals with the time and space complexity of algorithms in a weak message-passing model of distributed computing, which is a core topic in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of graph families, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also introduces a new complexity class for distributed computing, which could be of interest to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves the analysis of communication rounds, which could be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with the performance of algorithms in a distributed computing environment, which could be relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
